#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.16"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.16:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.16:0.2"
msgid "2. Rathakāravagga"
msgstr "2. The Chariotmaker"

# Three essential practices: sense restraint, moderation in eating, and wakefulness.
#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.16:0.3"
msgid "16. Apaṇṇakasutta"
msgstr "16. Guaranteed"

# BB has “unmistakeable”, which would mean “you can’t mistake it for something else”, which is incorrect. The basic meaning is it’s “win-win”, a situation where you can’t lose or fail.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: apaṇṇakapaṭipadaṃ → apaṇṇakataṃ paṭipadaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.16:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Tīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu apaṇṇakapaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno "
"hoti, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṃ khayāya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when a mendicant has three things their practice is guaranteed, "
"and they have laid the groundwork for ending the defilements."

msgctxt "an3.16:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.16:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, bhojane mattaññū hoti, "
"jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant guards the sense doors, eats in moderation, and is "
"dedicated to wakefulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.16:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant guard the sense doors?"

msgctxt "an3.16:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti "
"nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in "
"the features and details."

#. VAR: Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ → yatvādhikaraṇametaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an3.16:2.3"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight was left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "an3.16:2.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "an3.16:2.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "an3.16:2.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "an3.16:2.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "an3.16:2.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the "
"features and details."

msgctxt "an3.16:2.9"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "an3.16:2.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant guards the sense doors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.114"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.16:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhojane mattaññū hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant eat in moderation?"

msgctxt "an3.16:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āhāreti:"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant reflects properly on the food that they eat."

msgctxt "an3.16:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘neva davāya na madāya na maṇḍanāya na vibhūsanāya, yāvadeva imassa kāyassa "
"ṭhitiyā yāpanāya vihiṃsūparatiyā brahmacariyānuggahāya, iti purāṇañca "
"vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me bhavissati "
"anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to continue and "
"sustain this body, avoid harm, and support spiritual practice. So that I "
"will put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and "
"so that I will keep on living blamelessly and at ease.’"

msgctxt "an3.16:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhojane mattaññū hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant eats in moderation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.16:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant dedicated to wakefulness?"

msgctxt "an3.16:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu divasaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi "
"cittaṃ parisodheti, rattiyā paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi "
"dhammehi cittaṃ parisodheti, rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ dakkhiṇena passena "
"sīhaseyyaṃ kappeti pāde pādaṃ accādhāya sato sampajāno uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi "
"karitvā, rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ paccuṭṭhāya caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi "
"dhammehi cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant practices walking and sitting meditation by day, "
"purifying their mind from obstacles. In the evening, they continue to "
"practice walking and sitting meditation. In the middle of the night, they "
"lie down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of "
"the other—mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up. In the "
"last part of the night, they get up and continue to practice walking and "
"sitting meditation, purifying their mind from obstacles."

msgctxt "an3.16:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti."
msgstr "This is how a mendicant is dedicated to wakefulness."

msgctxt "an3.16:4.4"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu apaṇṇakapaṭipadaṃ "
"paṭipanno hoti, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṃ khayāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has these three things their practice is guaranteed, and "
"they have laid the groundwork for ending the defilements.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.16:4.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
